{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.20",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 20 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:1",
      "text": "There is a reproof that is not timely; and there is a person who is wise enough to keep silent.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:2",
      "text": "How good is it to reprove, rather than to be angry. He who confesses will be kept back from harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:4",
      "text": "As is the lust of a eunuch to deflower a virgin, so is he who executes judgments with violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:5",
      "text": "There is one who keeps silent and is found wise; and there is one who is hated for his much talk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:6",
      "text": "There is one who keeps silent, for he has no answer to make; And there is one who keeps silent, knowing when to speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:7",
      "text": "A wise man will be silent until his time has come, but the braggart and fool will miss his time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:8",
      "text": "He who uses many words will be abhorred. He who takes authority for himself will be hated in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:9",
      "text": "There is a prosperity that a man finds in misfortunes; and there is a gain that turns to loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:10",
      "text": "There is a gift that will not profit you; and there is a gift that pays back double.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:11",
      "text": "There are losses because of glory; and there is one who has lifted up his head from a low estate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:12",
      "text": "There is one who buys much for a little, and pays for it again sevenfold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:13",
      "text": "He who is wise in words will make himself beloved; but the pleasantries of fools will be wasted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:14",
      "text": "The gift of a fool will not profit you, for he looks for repayment many times instead of one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:15",
      "text": "He will give little and insult much. He will open his mouth like a crier. Today he will lend, and tomorrow he will ask for it back. Such a one is a hateful man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:16",
      "text": "The fool will say, “I have no friend, and I have no thanks for my good deeds. Those who eat my bread have an evil tongue.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:17",
      "text": "How often, and of how many, will he be laughed to scorn!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:18",
      "text": "A slip on a pavement is better than a slip with the tongue. So the fall of the wicked will come speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:19",
      "text": "A man without grace is a tale out of season. It will be continually in the mouth of the ignorant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:20",
      "text": "A parable from a fool’s mouth will be rejected; for he won’t tell it at the proper time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:21",
      "text": "There is one who is hindered from sinning through lack. When he rests, he will not be troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:22",
      "text": "There is one who destroys his soul through bashfulness. By a foolish countenance, he will destroy it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:23",
      "text": "There is one who for bashfulness makes promises to his friend; and he makes him his enemy for nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:24",
      "text": "A lie is an ugly blot on a person. It will be continually in the mouth of the ignorant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:25",
      "text": "A thief is better than a man who is continually lying, but they both will inherit destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:26",
      "text": "The destination of a liar is dishonor. His shame is with him continually.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:27",
      "text": "He who is wise in words will advance himself. And one who is prudent will please great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:28",
      "text": "He who tills his land will raise his harvest high. He who pleases great men will get pardon for iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:29",
      "text": "Favors and gifts blind the eyes of the wise, and as a muzzle on the mouth, turn away reproofs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:30",
      "text": "Wisdom that is hidden, and treasure that is out of sight— what profit is in either of them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.20.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:31",
      "text": "Better is a man who hides his folly than a man who hides his wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
